shadcn/ui is a highly popular open-source collection of reusable, accessible UI components built using Radix UI primitives and Tailwind CSS. It emphasizes copy-paste integration, allowing developers to easily incorporate and customize components into React, Vue, or other frameworks without heavy dependencies.

Tailwind CSS is a utility-first CSS framework that enables rapid UI development by providing low-level utility classes for styling elements directly in HTML, allowing for highly customizable and performant designs without predefined component styles.

ai_description: Magic UI is an open-source library of animated UI components and effects tailored for design engineers. It offers copy-paste ready elements with Framer Motion animations, built on Tailwind CSS and Radix UI, enabling quick integration of eye-catching interactions like gradients, particles, and hover effects into web apps.

DaisyUI is a popular open-source component library built on Tailwind CSS, offering pre-designed, themeable UI components like buttons, cards, and modals that speed up development while maintaining Tailwind's utility-first approach.

ai_description: Reaflow is a React-based library for constructing interactive workflow diagrams and flowcharts, featuring automatic layouts, customizable nodes and edges, and support for zooming, panning, and undo/redo operations.

Radix Primitives provides unstyled, accessible UI building blocks for React applications, focusing on behavior and accessibility rather than visuals. It's ideal for creating custom design systems, with components like dialogs, tooltips, and accordions that integrate seamlessly with any styling solution like Tailwind or CSS-in-JS.
stencil_patterns:
[{"name": "Dialog", "code": "import * as Dialog from '@radix-ui/react-dialog'

function App() {
  return (
    <Dialog.Root>
      <Dialog.Trigger>Open</Dialog.Trigger>
      <Dialog.Portal>
        <Dialog.Overlay />
        <Dialog.Content>
          <Dialog.Title>Dialog Title</Dialog.Title>
          <Dialog.Description>Dialog Description</Dialog.Description>
        </Dialog.Content>
      </Dialog.Portal>
    </Dialog.Root>
  )
}"}, {"name": "Tooltip", "code": "import * as Tooltip from '@radix-ui/react-tooltip'

function App() {
  return (
    <Tooltip.Provider>
      <Tooltip.Root>
        <Tooltip.Trigger>Hover me</Tooltip.Trigger>
        <Tooltip.Portal>
          <Tooltip.Content>Tooltip content</Tooltip.Content>
        </Tooltip.Portal>
      </Tooltip.Root>
    </Tooltip.Provider>
  )
}"}]
